16oz roasted red peppers
1c walnuts, toasted
1c bread crumbs
1t ground cumin
5 cloves garlic
2T tomato paste
2T chipotle peppers
1T lemon juice
1T pomegranate molasses (regular molasses in a pinch)
1t Worcestershire sauce
salt
2/3c olive oil

After toasting the walnuts in a pan, combine everything but olive oil into a food processor.  Blend to chunkiness, scraping sides as needed.  With processor on, slowly pour in olive oil, scraping sides and adding salt as needed.  Add some sriracha if more heat is needed.
